content.thinking:
Now I understand the issue. Looking at the three rules that try to fix the same problem:

1. `SpacingAroundCurlyRule` (line 118): uses `node.upsertWhitespaceBeforeMe(" ")` on the LBRACE node
2. `FunctionStartOfBodySpacingRule` (lines 113-117): uses `block.firstChildNode.prevLeaf(true)?.upsertWhitespaceAfterMe(" ")`
3. `FunctionSignatureRule` (lines 643-647): uses `functionBodyBlock.first().prevLeaf(true)?.upsertWhitespaceAfterMe(" ")`

The issue seems to be with `FunctionStartOfBodySpacingRule` and `FunctionSignatureRule`. They both use `prevLeaf(true)?.upsertWhitespaceAfterMe(" ")` instead of `upsertWhitespaceBeforeMe(" ")`.

Let me look more closely at `upsertWhitespaceAfterMe`:

```kotlin
public fun ASTNode.upsertWhitespaceAfterMe(text: String) {
    if (this is LeafElement) {
        if (this.elementType == WHITE_SPACE) {
            return replaceWhitespaceWith(text)
        }
        val next = treeNext ?: nextLeaf()
        if (next != null && next.elementType == WHITE_SPACE) {
            next.replaceWhitespaceWith(text)
        } else {
            PsiWhiteSpaceImpl(text).also { psiWhiteSpace ->
                (psi as LeafElement).rawInsertAfterMe(psiWhiteSpace)
            }
        }
    } else {
        lastChildLeafOrSelf().upsertWhitespaceAfterMe(text)
    }
}
```

The issue is that when calling `upsertWhitespaceAfterMe`, it first checks `treeNext` (sibling in the tree) before checking `nextLeaf()`. In the case where the previous leaf is `RPAR` (closing parenthesis) and it's part of a VALUE_PARAMETER_LIST, the `treeNext` might be a sibling within the VALUE_PARAMETER_LIST, not the next element after the function signature

.

